Congratulations to all members of our High School Science Olympiad Team for their 7th place finish (out of 37 teams) at the Columbia High School Science Olympiad Invitational on January 4. Collectively, the team took home 17 awards. Individual awards were as follows:
Zachary Calinda and Axel Roberts placed 2nd in the Wright Stuff;
Yasmin Chefridi, Kate Queen, and Jazarah Shim placed 2nd in Experimental Design;
Emily Salem and Lucian McMenemy placed 4th in Disease Detectives;
Sydnee Schilling and Tahlula Potter placed 4th in Anatomy and Physiology;
Dylan Wiswall and Zachary Calinda placed 5th in Gravity Vehicle;
Nelson DelTufo and Axel Roberts placed 5th in Dynamic Planet;
Yasmin Chefridi and Emily Salem placed 5th in Write It Do It; and
Joey Driscoll and Jason Zheng placed 6th in Sound of Music.
The next event is the regional competition on February 8.

